===Etymology===
{{PIE root|nl|wert}}
From {{inh|nl|dum|werden}}, from {{inh|nl|odt|werthan}}, from {{inh|nl|gem-pro|*werþaną}}, from {{inh|nl|ine-pro|*wértti}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|nl|/ˈʋɔrdə(n)/}}
* {{audio|nl|Nl-worden.ogg|audio}}
* {{hyphenation|nl|wor|den}}
* {{rhymes|nl|ɔrdən}}

===Verb===
{{nl-verb}}

# {{lb|nl|copulative}} to [[become]]; to [[get]]; to [[grow]]; to [[turn]]
#: {{ux|nl|Zij wilde altijd al lerares '''worden'''.|She always wanted to become a teacher.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|nl|Mijn broer '''wordt''' vandaag twintig.|My brother is turning twenty today.|inline=1}} 
#: {{ux|nl|Het '''wordt''' hier erg benauwd. Open de ramen alsjeblieft!|It's getting very stuffy in here. Please open the windows!|inline=1}} 
# {{lb|nl|transitive|auxiliary}} {{n-g|Used to form the [[imperfect tense]] of the [[passive voice]], together with a [[past participle]].}}
#: {{ux|nl|Ze '''worden''' gered.|They are being saved.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|nl|De muur '''werd''' geschilderd.|The wall was being painted.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|nl|De muur zal '''worden''' geschilderd.|The wall will be painted. / The wall is going to be painted.|inline=1}}

====Usage notes====
* The [[perfect tense]] passive is formed using {{m|nl|zijn}}, while ''worden'' matches English [[continuous]] constructions in meaning. Therefore, as in usage 2 above,
# ''Ze '''worden''' gered.'' translates to “They '''are being''' saved.”
# ''Ze '''werden''' gered''. translates to “They '''were being''' saved.”
# Consequently, ''Ze '''''zijn''''' gered.'' and ''Ze '''''waren''''' gered.'' would be translated as “They '''have been''' saved.” and “They '''had been''' saved.” respectively.

